# zero-arena-bacend hosts two services that DO NOT share configuration:
#
#   • dataset service   →  copy `.env.dataset.example` into `.env`
#   • oracle  service   →  copy `.env.oracle.example`  into `.env`
#
# In production they should run on different hosts. In dev, if you really
# need both in the same process, concatenate the two example files into
# `.env` by hand. They never need to share an OPERATOR_PRIVATE_KEY with
# an ORACLE_PRIVATE_KEY — those are different roles with different
# threat models.
#
# Either way: this file is a stub. Do not paste secrets here.
